<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-766] Tests that currently fail should be committed to the repository</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-766</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Current surefire test harness fails if any of the tests fails. Surefire allows tests to be ignored but the problem with that approach is the tests to be ignored are mentioned separately via build script .&lt;br/&gt;
A mechanics can be provided for OpenJPA tests that annotates a TestCase or specific methods such that failures of these tests are ignored.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This facility will help people to contribute tests in the repository that demonstrates a bug or Test Driven Development.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
